[[File:Admiral casino, King Street, Hammersmith.jpg|thumbnail|Admiral "casino", [[King Street, Hammersmith]], London]]
'''Admiral''' is a British gambling company, with high street venues and gambling websites. It is a subsidiary of Luxury Leisure (previously known as Nobles), which is owned in turn by [[Novomatic]].<ref name="coin-opcommunity.co.uk">{{cite web|url=http://www.coin-opcommunity.co.uk/news/14032-luxury-leisure-acquires-brian-newton-leisure/|title=Luxury Leisure acquires Brian Newton Leisure - Coin-Op Community|publisher=|accessdate=21 October 2016}}</ref>
Admiral have more than 1,500 outlets worldwide, including over 60 casinos.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.admiral-gaming.com/en?country=GB|title=Admiral-Gaming.com|first=www.admiral-gaming.com,|last=Datenkraft|publisher=|accessdate=21 October 2016}}</ref>
In 2015, Luxury Leisure bought Brian Newton Leisure Limited, and announced that all its trading locations would be rebranded as Admiral in 2016, including Sun Valley, Shoppers Pride and Newton's Amusements.<ref name="coin-opcommunity.co.uk"/>
Admiral have 29 "electronic casinos" in Serbia, where they have been based since 1994.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.admiral-srbija.com/en/about-us|title=About us|publisher=}}</ref>
