{{Infobox building | name = Nagashima Museum | native_name = 長島美術館 | image = Female Portrait by Fujishima Takeji (Nagashima Museum).jpg | caption = Portrait of a Woman by [[Fujishima Takeji]] | cost = | owner = | address = 3-42-18 Take | location_town = [[Kagoshima]], [[Kagoshima Prefecture]] | location_country = [[Japan]] | coordinates = {{coord|31.581771|N|130.532387|E|display=title,inline|format=dms|type:landmark_region:JP_scale:10000}} | opened_date = October 1989 | inauguration_date = | renovation_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | other_dimensions = | floor_count = | floor_area = | architect = | architecture_firm = | url = {{homepage|http://www.ngp.jp/nagashima-museum/}} }}
{{nihongo|'''Nagashima Museum'''|長島美術館|Nagashima bijutsukan}} opened in [[Kagoshima]], [[Kagoshima Prefecture]], Japan, in 1989, the centenary of the City's official foundation. Located on a hill overlooking [[Sakurajima]] and [[Kagoshima Bay]], at an elevation of 110 metres, the Museum's collection of some thousand objects amassed by businessman {{nihongo|Nagashima Kōsuke|[[:ja:長島公佑|長島公佑]]}}, includes works by [[Kuroda Seiki]], [[Rodin]], and [[Chagall]], as well as [[Satsuma ware]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bunka.nii.ac.jp/museums/detail/613 |script-title=ja:長島美術館 |trans-title=Nagashima Museum |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=17 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ngp.jp/nagashima-museum/hp_6/flame/f_gaiyo.htm |script-title=ja:概要 |trans-title=Outline |language=Japanese |publisher=Nagashima Museum |accessdate=17 October 2015}}</ref>
