'''''The Cats''''' ({{lang-it|'''I bastardi'''}}) is a 1968 [[crime film]] directed by [[Duccio Tessari]] and starring [[Rita Hayworth]].

==Cast==
* [[Giuliano Gemma]] as Jason
* [[Klaus Kinski]] as Adam
* [[Margaret Lee (British actress)|Margaret Lee]] as Karen
* [[Rita Hayworth]] as Martha
* [[Claudine Auger]] as Barbara
* [[Serge Marquand]] as Jimmy
* [[Umberto Raho]] as Doctor
* Carl Cik as Policeman

==Production==
The film was originally worked on under the title of ''The Cats''.{{sfn|Curti|2013|p=17}} The credits of the film state that the film is an Italian, French and West German co-production.{{sfn|Curti|2013|p=17}} Actor [[Dan van Husen]] stated that the film is actually an Italian-Spanish co-production with the working title being ''Los Gatos''.{{sfn|Curti|2013|p=17}} The film was predominantly shot in Spain, with opening sequences shot in the United States.{{sfn|Curti|2013|p=17}}

==Release==
''The Cats'' was released in Italy as ''I bastardi'' in 30 October 1968 where it was distributed by [[Warner Bros.-Seven Arts]].{{sfn|Curti|2013|p=15}} The film grossed a total of 702,781,000 [[Italian lira|Italian lire]] on its theatrical run in Italy.{{sfn|Curti|2013|p=15}} In 1969 it was released in France and West Germany on 25 May and 6 June respectively.{{sfn|Curti|2013|p=15}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmportal.de/en/movie/der-bastard_ea43d4a72c935006e03053d50b37753d|publisher=[[Filmportal.de]]|title=Der Portal|accessdate=26 February 2017|language=German}}</ref> The film was released on the [[Warner Archive Collection]] on DVD under the title ''The Cats''.{{sfn|Curti|2013|p=15}}

==Reception==
A contemporary review in the ''[[Monthly Film Bulletin]]'' commented that the film was "no more than an updated Italian Western with all the familiar sadistic ingredients" and that "apart from a quite competently staged desert car chase, [[Duccio Tessari]] (who showed real flair in ''[[A Pistol for Ringo]]'') directs as though he had never been behind the camera before"<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Bastardi, I|magazine=[[Monthly Film Bulletin]]|volume=36|issue=420|page=145|year=1969|publisher=[[British Film Institute]]}}</ref>

